U||ladle. That once conceded, I return to my exhortation. I repeat, brothers, I repeat, no zeal, no hubbub, no excess; even in witticisms, gayety, jollities, or plays on words. Listen to me. I have the prudence of Amphiara√ºs and the baldness of C√¶sar. There must be a limit, even to rebuses. Est modus in rebus.
