U||CHAPTER II‚ÄîFANTINE HAPPY
U||She made no movement of either surprise or of joy; she was joy itself. That simple question, ‚ÄúAnd Cosette?‚Äù was put with so profound a faith, with so much certainty, with such a complete absence of disquiet and of doubt, that he found not a word of reply. She continued:‚Äî
